{{Infobox lake | name = Batak Reservoir | image = Изглед към остров Голака от Цигов Чарк.jpg | caption = | image_bathymetry = | caption_bathymetry = | location = [[Rhodope Mountains]] | coords = {{coord|41|58|16|N|24|11|27|E|type:waterbody_region:BG}} | type = dam | inflow = | outflow = Matnitsa river | catchment = {{convert|432|km2|abbr=on}} | basin_countries = [[Bulgaria]] | length = | width = | area = {{convert|22|km2|abbr=on}} | depth = | max-depth = {{convert|35|m|abbr=on}} <dam height> | volume = {{convert|310|hm3|abbr=on}} | residence_time = | shore = | elevation = {{convert|1107|m|abbr=on}} | frozen = | islands = | sections = | cities = [[Tsigov Chark]] }} The '''Batak Dam''' ({{lang-bg|язовир Батак}}) is located in the [[Rhodope Mountains]] and is the third largest in [[Bulgaria]]. It attracts many tourists and fishermen, and the resort [[Tsigov Chark]] was built on its shore. The lake is situated just above the historic [[Batak, Bulgaria|town of the same name]].
There is a [[hydroelectricity|hydro-electric power]] plant at Batak, and it is close to [[Pazardzhik]] and [[Plovdiv]].
