'''Dushyant Mahendrabhai Patel''' (born 1958) is an [[Indian-American]] businessman served as president of the company called AM2PAT Inc. based in [[Raleigh]], [[North Carolina]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Office of Criminal Investigations (OCI) Most Wanted Fugitives |url=https://www.fda.gov/ICECI/CriminalInvestigations/OCIsMostWantedFugitives/ucm389556.htm#patel |website=[[FDA]] |accessdate=13 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180908011526/https://www.fda.gov/ICECI/CriminalInvestigations/OCIsMostWantedFugitives/ucm389556.htm#patel#patel |archive-date=2018-09-08 |dead-url=no |df= }}</ref> Under his presidency, the company sold untested syringes of [[heparin]] that were tied to the deaths of at least 5 people and the hospitalizations of hundreds.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Palmer |first1=Eric |title=FDA's 'Most Wanted Fugitives': The agency wants your help finding these bad players |url=https://www.fiercepharma.com/regulatory/fda-s-most-wanted-fugitives-agency-wants-your-help-finding-these-bad-players |website=www.fiercepharma.com |accessdate=13 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613084806/https://www.fiercepharma.com/regulatory/fda-s-most-wanted-fugitives-agency-wants-your-help-finding-these-bad-players# |archive-date=2018-06-13 |dead-url=no |df= }}</ref>
Patel is among [[FDA Most Wanted Fugitives|the top ten fugitives]] sought by the United States [[Food and Drug Administration]]'s [[Office of Criminal Investigations]] (OCI).<ref name=fda>{{cite web |title=FDA-OCI Presents 11 Most Wanted Fugitives, Seeks Help in Catching Fake Drugs Criminals – Partnership for Safe Medicines |url=https://www.safemedicines.org/2014/09/fda-oci-presents-11-most-wanted-fugitives-seeks-help-in-catching-fake-drugs-criminals-9-10-14.html |website=www.safemedicines.org |accessdate=4 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160803195052/http://www.safemedicines.org/2014/09/fda-oci-presents-11-most-wanted-fugitives-seeks-help-in-catching-fake-drugs-criminals-9-10-14.html# |archive-date=2016-08-03 |dead-url=no |df= }}</ref>
