'''Pattern glare''' is a form of [[visual discomfort]],<ref>Wilkins, A., Nimmo-Smith, I., Tait, A., Mcmanus, Christopher, Sala, S. D., Tilley, A., Arnold, K. et al. (1984). A neurological basis for visual discomfort. Brain, 107, 989-1017.</ref> arising from viewing repetitively striped patterns, such as those of [[op art]]. Instead of the patterns' appearing as they are, they may appear to move, to shimmer, or to vary in shape over time.

